OL,6,F"Trading Standards teams across the UK
OL,7,Fare working tirelessly to disrupt
OL,8,Fthese operations but we need the
OL,9,Fpublic to stay alert, talk to loved
OL,10,Fones about the risks and report
OL,11,Fanything suspicious."
OL,13,FWhich? consumer law spokeswoman Lisa
OL,14,FWebb said: "You shouldn't have to
OL,15,Fworry about your own voice being used
OL,16,Fagainst you in this way but sadly
OL,17,Fwe've reached a stage where every
OL,18,Fphone call must be treated with
OL,19,Fsuspicion. If you get any calls out of
OL,20,Fthe blue, don't be afraid to hang up,
OL,21,Fgenuine callers won't mind.
